{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778339177,"nonce":"gd3ALtUyeMDg0Pm7IPKDOXhsAA8=","message":"## Matrix expanded from 3 to 6 cells\n\nThe previous loss-history subagent (/tmp/flavor_ab_review/findings/loss_history.md)\nidentified two cost-structure changes that may drive the inter-replicate variance\nobserved in the current matrix:\n\n1. **Terminal-step velocity penalty was dropped** (historical `effector_final_velocity`\n   fired only at t=T; current `effector_vel_late` spreads penalty across [go+80, T]).\n   The window formulation admits diverse stopping strategies and allows multiple local\n   optima to minimise the objective — replicates can find different solutions.\n\n2. **Position discount changed shape** (historical `(t/T)^6` concentrated 98% of\n   weight in the last 30% of the trial; current flat-running + modest cosine ramp\n   creates a broader basin with more local minima and more sensitivity to batch order).\n\n### New cells added\n\n| # | Run label | Anti-anticipation lever | Loss-shape variant |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | `gru__jerk` | none (control) | current default |\n| 2 | `gru__jerk_motor_pre` | `--nn-output-pre-go 1e-2` | current default |\n| 3 | `gru__jerk_smooth_high` | `--nn-hidden-derivative 1e2` | current default |\n| 4 | `gru__jerk_motor_smooth_combo` | both #2 and #3 | current default |\n| 5 | `gru__jerk_loss_v_terminal` | none | Variant A: `--effector-final-vel 1.0 --effector-vel-late 0.0` |\n| 6 | `gru__jerk_loss_historical` | none | Variant B: `--effector-final-vel 1.0 --effector-vel-late 0.0 --effector-pos-running 0.0 --effector-pos-late-weight 1.0 --effector-pos-late-final-scale 6.0 --effector-pos-late-start-step 0` |\n\nCell 4 (motor+smooth combo) was also added to the original 3 cells to test whether\nthe two anti-anticipation strategies are additive.\n\n### Predicted outcomes for Variants A and B\n\n- **Variant A** (terminal velocity only, position unchanged): Predicted moderate variance\n  reduction. The surgical t=T velocity signal is an identifying constraint. Should reduce\n  inter-replicate variance in late-trajectory shape and post-hold drift. Predicted\n  within-cell RMSE: comparable to or better than the best of cells 1-3.\n\n- **Variant B** (full historical shape): Predicted largest effect. The steep cosine ramp\n  (start_step=0, final_scale=6.0) recreates the (t/T)^6 end-heavy profile almost exactly.\n  If this works it is the cleanest test of the hypothesis. Biggest behavioural change; may\n  converge to different reach kinematics than the default-loss cells.\n\n### Updated decision criteria\n\nKeep prior pass criteria from the 3-cell pre-reg (A, B, C). Add:\n\n- If Variants A or B achieve within-cell RMSE \u003c min(cells 1-4), **recommend adopting the\n  historical loss shape as the new training default**. This would close the\n  basin-selection component of the smoothness umbrella (efc4d68).\n\n- If Variant A beats the default but Variant B does not (or vice versa), characterise\n  which component (terminal-step velocity vs. end-heavy position discount) is the operative\n  constraint; adjust the default accordingly.\n\n### Implementation\n\nCLI patch committed in branch feature/loss-shape-cli-and-6cell-matrix (commit 53c5159).\nNew flags: --effector-final-vel, --effector-vel-late, --effector-pos-running,\n--effector-pos-late-weight, --effector-pos-late-final-scale, --effector-pos-late-start-step.\nAll defaults reproduce current behaviour (no change for existing runs).\nNew RUN_PLAN at results/part2_5/runpod/anti_anticipation_loss_shape_6cell/RUN_PLAN.md.\nCross-ref: efc4d68 (smoothness umbrella), 5acdaae (anti-anticipation strategy menu).","files":null}]}